Ochieng and his seven accomplices knocked at Otieno’s door before they broke in after he declined to open, police said. Otieno could only identify three, including Ochieng, who allegedly stabbed him all over his body.
His accomplices ransacked Otieno’s house while he went on stabbing him, police said. Otieno raised the alarm during the robbery but nobody responded until police arrived at the scene, police said.
The officers took him to Kenyatta National Hospital where he was admitted for two days.



