Police said Ochieng was wanted for more robberies before he robbed Otieno and he committed others thereafter while still being sought.
Ochieng was arrested by police officers on patrol and allegedly found with a knife and  32 rolls of bhang.
After Ochieng was taken to the Ruaraka Police Station, police identified him as the suspect behind a series of robberies. He admitted that his accomplices had robbed Otieno during police investigations, police said.
Ochieng was also charged with possession of narcotics.
He denied the charges before Senior Principal Magistrate Angelo Kithinji.
The suspect was freed on a Sh500,000 bond with a surety of similar amount without an option of cash bail. The case will be mentioned on January 11, 2021.



